# Codespell config — English-primary code paths only. departments/ and
# wiki/ carry bilingual pt-PT content and framework/person/brand proper
# nouns that drown the signal in false positives ("nome" -> "gnome").
#
# That exclusion lives in `skip` below rather than in the caller's path
# list, so the evidence gate (core/governance/evidence_checks.py) honours
# it — the gate spellchecks the changed files of a diff and cannot know
# which roots are bilingual.
#
# The globs are listed twice, bare and `*/`-prefixed, because codespell
# fnmatches the path exactly as constructed (codespell_lib/_codespell.py):
# a walk from `codespell .` yields `./departments/...`, which the bare
# `departments/*` pattern does not match. Each invocation style needs
# its own form — `*/departments/*` for the walk,
# `departments/*` for an explicit path — so the two agree.
#
# ignore-words-list entries are all verified false positives:
#   te/vai/ser/erro/cliente/relevante — pt-PT fixtures (sycophancy detector,
#     synapse L2.5 tests, checkpoint tests)
#   strat — the /strat department command
#   ines — Ines, Landing squad lead agent
#   infp — MBTI type in agent DNA
#   skool — the Skool community platform
#   coo — Chief Operations Officer
#   sive — sive.rs (Derek Sivers' site)
#   fo — schtasks /FO output-format flag (Windows scheduler)
#   unparseable/implementor — accepted English variants
#   componentes/comandos/classe/meu — pt-PT effect-object lexicon in
#     core/governance/phantom_action_check.py (P0 2026-07-08)
#   fase/fases — the pt-PT fixture at tests/python/test_phantom_action_check.py,
#     the pt-PT passages of docs/strategy/, and a pt-PT trigger string under
#     plugins/. Those roots are NOT skipped: their English prose still
#     benefits from the check, so the words are ignored instead.
#   orgin/metdata/datas — INTENTIONAL misspellings in core/skills/provenance.py:
#     the provenance parser detects these exact typos (metadatas:, orgin:) so a
#     laundered skill cannot slip through; they appear in the docstring, the
#     _METADATA_TYPO regex (metadatas?), and the test fixtures.
[codespell]
ignore-words-list = te,strat,unparseable,ines,infp,skool,coo,vai,ser,erro,cliente,relevante,sive,fo,implementor,componentes,comandos,classe,meu,fase,fases,orgin,metdata,datas
skip = *.lock,*.svg,*/node_modules,*/__pycache__,departments/*,*/departments/*,wiki/*,*/wiki/*
